<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,303,989,1015]" box="[189,303,989,1015]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,989,1015]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,989,1015]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1035,1133]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authority="Morassi &amp; Nappo &amp; Bonfitto, 2017" authorityName="Morassi &amp; Nappo &amp; Bonfitto" authorityYear="2017" box="[189,364,1035,1062]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Otitoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hadra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,364,1035,1062]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Otitoma hadra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[373,465,1036,1062]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is readily distinguished from its described congeners by its rather small, thick shell (about 
<quantity box="[333,400,1070,1097]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
in maximum length), with a relatively large protoconch and well developed sculpture (both spiral and axial).
</paragraph>
